        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "intro_2",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "From the earth: Greetings",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 2.47,
      "endTime": 10.34
    },
    {
      "id": "intro_3",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "Which life forms are most likely to develop on a distant planet?",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 10.35,
      "endTime": 17.4,
      "analysis": {
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "intro_4",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "Recent developments in astronomy have made it possible to detect planets in our own Milky Way and in other galaxies.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 17.41,
      "endTime": 26.54,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s1",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "This is a major achievement because, in relative terms, planets are very small and do not emit light.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 26.55,
      "endTime": 34.98,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "This",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "这，这个"
          },
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          },
          {
            "word": "Very",
            "pos": "adv.",
            "meaning": "很，非常"
          },
          {
            "word": "Not",
            "pos": "adv.",
            "meaning": "不，不是"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s2",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "Finding planets is proving hard enough, but finding life on them will prove infinitely more difficult.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 34.99,
      "endTime": 42.51,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s3",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "The first question to answer is whether a planet can actually support life.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 42.52,
      "endTime": 48.54,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s4",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "In our own solar system, for example, Venus is far to hot and Mars is far too cold to support life.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 48.55,
      "endTime": 57.02,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          },
          {
            "word": "Hot",
            "pos": "adj.",
            "meaning": "热的"
          },
          {
            "word": "Too",
            "pos": "adv.",
            "meaning": "也"
          },
          {
            "word": "Cold",
            "pos": "adj.",
            "meaning": "冷的"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s5",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "Only the Earth provides ideal conditions, and even here it has taken more than four billion years for plant and animal life to evolve.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 57.03,
      "endTime": 68.34,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Here",
            "pos": "adv.",
            "meaning": "这里"
          },
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s6",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "Whether a planet can support life depends on the size and brightness of its star, that is its 'sun'.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 68.35,
      "endTime": 75.67,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "That",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "那个"
          },
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s7",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "Imagine a star up to twenty times larger, brighter and hotter than our own sun.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 75.68,
      "endTime": 82.24,
      "analysis": {
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s8",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "A planet would have to be a very long way from it to be capable of supporting life.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 82.25,
      "endTime": 87.91,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Very",
            "pos": "adv.",
            "meaning": "很，非常"
          },
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s9",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "Alternatively, if the star were small,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 87.92,
      "endTime": 91.08
    },
    {
      "id": "s10",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "the life-supporting planet would have to have a close orbit round it and also provide the perfect conditions for life forms to develop.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 91.09,
      "endTime": 101.36,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s11",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "But how would we find such a planet?",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 101.37,
      "endTime": 104.72,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "How",
            "pos": "adv.",
            "meaning": "怎样，如何"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s12",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "At present, there is no telescope in existence that is capable of detecting the presence of life.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 104.73,
      "endTime": 112.37,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "At",
            "pos": "prep.",
            "meaning": "在...（小地点/时刻）"
          },
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          },
          {
            "word": "That",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "那个"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s13",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "The development of such a telescope will be one of the great astronomical projects of the 21st century.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 112.38,
      "endTime": 121.14,
      "analysis": {
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s14",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "It is impossible to look for life on another planet using earth-based telescopes.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 121.15,
      "endTime": 127.33,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          },
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          },
          {
            "word": "Look",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "看"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s15",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "Our own warm atmosphere and the heat generated by the telescope",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 127.34,
      "endTime": 131.97,
      "analysis": {
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s16",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "would make it impossible to detect objects as small as planets.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 131.98,
      "endTime": 137.09,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s17",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "Even a telescope in orbit round the earth, like the very successful Hubble telescope,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 137.1,
      "endTime": 143.31,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Very",
            "pos": "adv.",
            "meaning": "很，非常"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s18",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "would not be suitable because of the dust particles in our solar system.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 143.32,
      "endTime": 149.02,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Not",
            "pos": "adv.",
            "meaning": "不，不是"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s19",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "A telescope would have to be as far away as the planet Jupiter to look for life in outer space,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 149.03,
      "endTime": 156.54,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Look",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "看"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s20",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "because the dust becomes thinner the further we travel towards the outer edges of our own solar system.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 156.55,
      "endTime": 163.96,
      "analysis": {
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s21",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "Once we detected a planet, we would have to find a way of blotting out the light from its star,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 163.97,
      "endTime": 170.46,
      "analysis": {
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s22",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "so that we would be able to 'see' the planet properly and analyse its atmosphere.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 170.47,
      "endTime": 176.37,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "That",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "那个"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s23",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "In the first instance, we would be looking for plant life, rather than 'little green men'.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 176.38,
      "endTime": 182.98,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Green",
            "pos": "adj.",
            "meaning": "绿色的"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s24",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "The life forms most likely to develop on a planet would be bacteria.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 182.99,
      "endTime": 188.84
    },
    {
      "id": "s25",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "It is bacteria that have generated the oxygen we breathe on earth.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 188.85,
      "endTime": 194.07,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          },
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          },
          {
            "word": "That",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "那个"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s26",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "For most of the earth's history they have been the only form of life on our planet.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 194.08,
      "endTime": 199.94,
      "analysis": {
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s27",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "As Earth-dwellers, we always cherish the hope that we will be visited by little green men and that we will be able to communicate with them.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 199.95,
      "endTime": 210.23,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "That",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "那个"
          },
          {
            "word": "Green",
            "pos": "adj.",
            "meaning": "绿色的"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s28",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "But this hope is always in the realms of science fiction.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 210.24,
      "endTime": 215.37,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "This",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "这，这个"
          },
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s29",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "If we were able to discover lowly forms of life like bacteria on another planet, it would completely change our view of ourselves.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 215.38,
      "endTime": 225.4,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s30",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "As Daniel Goldin of NASA observed, 'Finding life elsewhere would change everything.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 225.41,
      "endTime": 232.32
    },
    {
      "id": "s31",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "No human endeavour or thought would be unchanged by it.'",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 232.33,
      "endTime": 237.33,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
}
